1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,600
hi everyone my name is Jia Wen

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:05,600
tonight I want to share how I track my spending

3
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,000
every lunch here costs around 15 ringgit

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,700
and some days it goes up to 20 ringgit

5
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:13,700
I used to record everything in a spreadsheet

6
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,100
almost 80 percent of my entries were wrong

7
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,800
so I decided to write a small program

8
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,800
it started as a weekend software project

9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,200
the agent reads my receipts from Telegram

10
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,900
then it stores every record in a database

11
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:29,900
the database runs on my old laptop at home

12
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:32,300
I use Claude to extract the amounts

13
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,000
actually I write most of the code with Claude Code

14
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,000
the whole flow is wired up through MCP

15
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,400
the MCP server exposes three simple tools

16
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,100
all the source code is on GitHub

17
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:46,100
the skill instructions live in a SKILL.md file

18
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,500
without a network connection nothing syncs

19
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:51,200
so I added an offline queue for the data

20
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:54,200
every month it generates a short video summary

21
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,600
the video shows where my money actually went

22
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:59,300
last month food was 40 percent of everything

23
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:02,300
transport was another 25 percent

24
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,700
that information completely changed my habits

25
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:07,400
I cut my coffee budget by 100 ringgit

26
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,400
the program now runs every single night

27
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:12,800
it posts the summary back to Telegram

28
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,500
my friends asked if the software is hard to maintain

29
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,500
honestly Claude Code does most of the maintenance

30
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:20,900
thank you and find me on GitHub if you want the code
